<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Rumors of rare armor</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Samien (Fenin Ro)">Samien (Fenin Ro)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:08 p.m. 7/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Rumors of rare armor<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/fennin_ro.cgi?read=227" TARGET=_self>Rumors of rare armor</A> (Dekadence)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>I'm a wizard and I don't mind telling people where to get stuff... I don't have alot of good stuff but that's because I don't like to camp.

<P>Rubi armour is found in Cazic Thule. This is the Lizard Man Temple off of Feerrot. This is in an evil zone so you have to watch out for the guards because, as you can imagine, they hit hard. I have several marks on my armrour from them.
<P>The Rubi stuff is on what everybody calls the rares, which are rare named spawns like the Tae Ew Templer, The Steel Golem, The Avatar of Fear and the Anchorn (sp?). I hear that Rubi is lighter than bronze with better AC and the breastplate (from the steel golem) increases your health regen rate. That's all I know except that most of the time there is a group of dispicable kill stealers that try for all the rares and things can turn into a fre for all real quick.
<P>Hope that helps.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
